Pets not zoning is ok for the most part from a PvE standpoint, but I think PvP mages get a bit of a shaft when it comes to zoning. I have no PvP experience though. Also, for zones designed to be zone in and fight, such as PoF(not that I'd zone a pet into PoF anyway, but..), it's a slightly unfair penalty<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I have a 55 mage on Sullon Zek, and I have to say that not being able to zone with a pet really hurts.  Of course, it hurts any pet dependent class, but it effects us the most, I think.  Mages are one of the least popular classes on SZ; I'm not sure there's a class that has fewer numbers 50+, (obviously not counting Beastlords) except possibly Shadowknight (which is actually a very nice class in PVP, but it's restricted to one team, and I guess people don't like them a lot in PVE) and I think that the amount of prep time that's required before a mage can fight is a big part of why.  It's certainly not the only reason,  casters as a whole have problems solo versus tanks, but it still hurts.  PVP fights involve a lot of chasing people across zonelines, zoning in quickly and attacking opponents, etc.  Often the 15 second prep time (at the very least, not even figuring in buffing your pet, or summoning a blanket for it) before a mage can fight is completely impossible to manage.  And in that case, it's either choose not to fight or act as a low quality wizard.  No other class has this problem to this degree.  <br>
<br>
I don't expect VI to make class changes based upon PVP results (it would be nice, but they've shown they won't, so it would be foolish to expect it), but still, this is something that could help out mages a lot on PVP servers, and it doesn't seem like it would be too unbalancing to the PVE servers.  My 2 cents. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thedwellerindarkness>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(1/26/02 1:55:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pet zoning, PvP</span><hr size=1> Actually I too play on a PvP server, Rallos. A mage with a pet up has few options open once a pet gets rooted, snared, or worse yet charmed and poofed. A mage with no pet up (such as after a zone) has almost no options. Even worse is after a teleport, as there isn't even the safety of the zone line to retreat back through if you find yourself being attacked.<br>
<br>
 I try to stay away from PvP reasoning when asking for changes, because we do know that PvP is at the bottom of Verant's list of things to consider. I would think there are enough PvE balance issues to warrant Verant's efforts here.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thedwellerindarkness>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 4:05:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet zoning, PvP</span><hr size=1> &quot;Magicians summon things out of the raw elements and it can only be sustained so long at a time, so they have to summon new ones when they zone.&quot;<br>
<br>
In other words &quot;We don't want to give you a good answer, so the answer is MAGIC.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umrtattortot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Tattortot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 7:14:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet Zoning</span><hr size=1> From my understanding, the reason why beastlord's pet lost the buffs was because the original pet dies and a new one is automatically created when the player finished zoning. Well if that is the case, doesn't that mean if we had zoning pets, it would lose both the equipment on it and the buffs it had?<br>
<br>
Main reason why I would want a zoning pet is because if I had to zone right after making an epic pet, I would have to wait for the recast time of the epic weapon.<br>
<br>
I would rather have a pet that comes back after you go ld. Was faction hunting in droga awhile back and went ld. Came back with a few gobbys on me and had to gate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
